Description: Bought new at Mark's Guitars in San Diego, I walked in expecting to buy a Les Paul but this guitar was so resonant and beautiful I couldn't pass it up. Unfortunately, I came to understand I just can't play the longer Fender scale length well, so am very reluctantly selling it.  I'm just a beginner who is practicing chords and basic songs/riffs, so this guitar saw very light and careful use and is absolutely in like new condition. There are no scratches or dings, it functions perfectly and sounds like a dream.  As is typical with the very thin EJ pickguards, this one didn't lay perfectly flat and had a rough edge when I bought it and it's never been a big enough deal for me to replace it. Includes all the case candy, which has never installed or used, including: -chrome bridge cover -tremolo arm -certificate of authenticity (w/serial #) -black leather strap -Fender instrument cable I'm also including the original receipt (date of purchase 12/26/17), dealer price/inventory tags, and Loxx nickel-finish strap locks I installed (along with the stock Fender hardware) and a couple sets of Fender 250R strings (10s).
Title: Fender Eric Johnson Signature Stratocaster - MINT/PERFECT 2 color sunburst
ConditionDescription: Flawless, mint, no scratches, buckle rush, or dings. Bought new and always kept in case, only played a few times, strings changed once. Absolutely no wear from use or handling. Locking hardshell case also mint condition.
